le of points where we had inserted the winged connectors in main line.  These were fixed easily with a bit of twisting and some m-seal.But all things are not perfect. The red sprinklers can be regulated to some extent - but not like the shower in your bathroom. They keep dribbling or overshooting. However, we found a good use for these and snuck them between two half round pots, thus serving both pots with one pipe. See picThe black drippers can be unscrewed for cleaning - but you can’t stop them from dripping. So don’t try.Tips:1. Don’t start off cutting this into pieces straightaway. Fit and test one line before taking up the rest.2. Draw a rough plan of how the layout will be, where do you need T connectors and elbow bends and where all you need to regulate or stop the flow of water.3. If possible don’t use the tap connector supplied by Cingaro to connect the system to main tap. Use a soft hose pipe and a clamp for this. See pic.4. Fixing the winged t connectors into the 4 mm pipe is a nightmare with bare hands. Your thumb and fingers will get sore in half an hour. Soften the end of the 4 mm pipe by heating it slightly, and use a gardening glove to twist the t in. Remember that the slanted end goes into the 16 mm pipe, straight end into the 4 mm pipe.5. You will need to figure out the time you need to leave this on by trial and error. A 9” plastic pot needs about 100-300 ml water. The drippers are rated for 1 litre per hour. So if you leave the system on for about 5-15 minutes, your plants will get enough water.6. If you have small and large pots, you can order other types of drippers separately and use them on the same line. Green ones are rated at 2 litres per hour.7. If you want to fit it and forget it, you will have to order a timer valve. You can get a multi outlet timer valve also, if you want separate times and setting for leafy and flowering plants.Because the system is so flexible, it will very nearly do everything you ask it to do. Except plucking the flowers! ','True','B07GMVDTH1','POSITIVE'),(1018,4,'Very Good...But....','https://www.amazon.in/gp/customer-reviews/REM11X8HEX8CP/ref=cm_cr_arp_d_rvw_ttl?ie=UTF8&ASIN=B07GMVDTH1','Reviewed in India on 3 May 2024','The drip irrigation kit provided is very much useful... But there was only 25 pin connectors.. 5 were missing.. So I can use it only for watering 25 plants. Given 30 dummies instead of 10 shown in the product page... ( -1 star for the carelessness during the packing ). Started watering within half an hour of the delivery..ie connecting the components is so easy... There is a little water leakage but I hope it will stop within 5 to 6 days as mentioned in the product video...','True','B07GMVDTH1','NEUTRAL'),(1019,5,'Awesome','https://www.amazon.in/gp/customer-reviews/R3LDKTP7N3XCUW/ref=cm_cr_arp_d_rvw_ttl?ie=UTF8&ASIN=B07GMVDTH1','Reviewed in India on 16 June 2024','Very good quality... Easy to install.. value for money ','True','B07GMVDTH1','POSITIVE'),(1020,3,'VAalue for money, good product material but Quantity mismatch/missing','https://www.amazon.in/gp/customer-reviews/R30X1F1SIVQSPS/ref=cm_cr_arp_d_rvw_ttl?ie=UTF8&ASIN=B07GMVDTH1','Reviewed in India on 2 July 2024','HI All,I have ordered similar kit for 10 Plants and then ordered for 60 plants.Quality of Material is good, Easy to install and works well as suggested.However the 30M 4MM pipe is missing.I have left a message to Seller and also contacted Amazon helpline to share this feedback and provide the missing pipe.But no Response. @Seller - pls check the items before being shipped to prevent this hassle.','True','B07GMVDTH1','NEGATIVE'),(1021,4,'Quite useful.','https://www.amazon.in/gp/customer-reviews/R1TTJ518H2J7LQ/ref=cm_cr_arp_d_rvw_ttl?ie=UTF8&ASIN=B07GMVDTH1','Reviewed in India on 25 April 2024','Been a couple days i have used this and here are my observations:Fit - all fittings fit snugly with no much leakage. The system does not require a high flow rate/pressure. I connect it to my main water line at flow rate of about 1l/min and it works without hassles. The loosest fit is the dripper which is at risk to come loose if high water pressure is used.Adjustability : This I would consider somewhat of a con in that it\'s not a drip irrigation. The flow rate at the slowest from the dripper is at around 49ml/min, which is quite high. So within 10mins u will have watered about 500ml . Further there is no option to turn off the dripper. To stop flow u need to unplug the dripper and block the 4mm pipe.Appearance: Quite aesthetic looking if u route the main supply pipe properly. My suggestion here would be to place the main pipe (16mm) at a higher level and the 4mm pipe to be connected along the bottom to go downwards. (Have ordered more main pipe and will post photos once my system is set)Value for money: definitely as at ₹500-600 for 30 plants, u can just turn on the mains and forget it for the time u want to water.(else u lose around 1/2 hr watering each plant individially) If u use an irrigation timer even this much attention will not be required.To sum up:Pros:Works as advertisedFit it and forget it - hence time savingDoesn\'t require much water pressure.Cons:Dripper fitting is on the looser sideSlowest drip rate is ~50ml/minNo option to turn the dripper off.Suggestions:Use sprinkler type end drippers along with these drip ones if u need to cover a wider ground area(e.g. in gardens where u might have a mix of plants growing on the ground and in pots)','True','B07GMVDTH1','POSITIVE'),(1022,5,'Excellent Quality Product','https://www.amazon.in/gp/customer-reviews/R1GSP86SWA522C/ref=cm_cr_arp_d_rvw_ttl?ie=UTF8&ASIN=B07GMVDTH1','Reviewed in India on 18 May 2024','The media could not be loaded.\n                My name Dhananjay Singh, I ordered this drip irrigation system for our Dhyan Ashram\'s small phoolwadi, The quality of the product is very good, the fitting, adjustability is good. I installed it myself, so easy because they provide all tiny instruments requi