under the weight, which confirms predecessing reviewers.- the pump shaft is not tight and rather loosely put into the gun unit; hence wobbling around, which makes it prone for breaking the unit sooner or later as it introduces an angle to the pump shaft. Every engineer will cnfirm those physics.- the adjustable nozzle is of poor quality. It is half metal, half plastic. If you dont tight up the lower plasic part the bottle will just release water and pressure without even touching the trigger. The metal part is borderline to fall apart when setting it to a mist sparey setting in oppose to a straight beam of water. You twist ti a millimeter too far, it comes off. If you twisst it a millimeter too less, its no mist spray any more- the biggest disappointment is however the way it is designed to process the water. That indeed is a design failure as you cannot use the spray bottle in an angle if your water level falls below 1L. Reason is, the internal feeder pipe will then be outside the water level and just suck up the airpressure rather than the water. It only works if you keep the bottle in a perfect vertical, leveled position. Which in effect defeats the entire purpose of that spray bottle.On a side note, you cannot use the bottle upside down. Ok, that was not mentioned in the product description, but I guess you should know, especially if you have a little sophistication in gardening.Thus please save your cash and spend it on a different product. Maybe even spend an extra dime to pick up a quality product, rather than polluting our environment by throwing it away sooner or later.P.S. funniest thing is, it has something like \'meet quality\' printed on it - irony in its purest form','True','B01HQCKG4O','NEGATIVE'),(1747,3,'Nozzle not working','https://www.amazon.in/gp/customer-reviews/R1SQRV407HS8J8?ASIN=B01HQCKG4O','Reviewed in India on 29 May 2024','Nozzle not working properly after 3-4 uses.','True','B01HQCKG4O','NEGATIVE'),(1748,5,'Quality','https://www.amazon.in/