April 2024','If you are considering to purchase this pressure spray bottle, then please reconsider NOT to do so. I bought it to maintain my plants and give them a regular shower, but I am deeply disapointed by the quality and function of it. Here is my reason why:- the handle is really instable and weak for a fully filled (2L) bottle, the entire gun (spray/pump/handle) unit is low quality and super cheaply produced. The handle bends under the weight, which confirms predecessing reviewers.- the pump shaft is not tight and rather loosely put into the gun unit; hence wobbling around, which makes it prone for breaking the unit sooner or later as it introduces an angle to the pump shaft. Every engineer will cnfirm those physics.- the adjustable nozzle is of poor quality. It is half metal, half plastic. If you dont tight up the lower plasic part the bottle will just release water and pressure without even touching the trigger. The metal part is borderline to fall apart when setting it to a mist sparey setting in oppose to a straight beam of water. You twist ti a millimeter too far, it comes off. If you twisst it a millimeter too less, its no mist spray any more- the biggest disappointment is however the way it is designed to process the water. That indeed is a design failure as you cannot use the spray bottle in an angle if your water level falls below 1L. Reason is, the internal feeder pipe will then be outside the water level and just suck up the airpressure rather than the water. It only works if you keep the bottle in a perfect vertical, leveled position. Which in effect defeats the entire purpose of that spray bottle.On a side note, you cannot use the bottle upside down. Ok, that was not mentioned in the product description, but I guess you should know, especially if you have a little sophistication in gardening.Thus please save your cash and spend it on a different product. Maybe even spend an extra dime to pick up a quality product, rather than polluting our environment by throwing it away sooner or later.P.S. funniest thing is, it has something like \'meet quality\' printed on it - irony in its purest form','True','B01HQCKG4O','NEGATIVE'),(3390,3,'Nozzle not working','https://www.amazon.in/gp/customer-reviews/R1SQRV407HS8J8?ASIN=B01HQCKG4O','Reviewed in India on 29 May 2024','Nozzle not working properly after 3-4 uses.','True','B01HQCKG4O','NEGATIVE'),(3391,5,'Quality','https://www.amazon.in/gp/customer-reviews/R25DS2PVSIVFAG?ASIN=B01HQCKG4O','Reviewed in India on 23 July 2024','Product quality is good and easy to operate','True','B01HQCKG4O','POSITIVE'),(3392,4,'Good quality product','https://www.amazon.in/gp/customer-reviews/R227EG4SBAKI7J?ASIN=B01HQCKG4O','Reviewed in India on 10 December 2023','First supplied product was with a defective spray nozzle which was promptly replaced by the seller immediately. Product needs to be despatched with a slightly stronger packing as it comes with a thin plastic cover which might give room for damages while transporting. Basically it\'s a good product.','True','B01HQCKG4O','POSITIVE'),(3393,5,'Very good and durable','https://www.amazon.in/gp/customer-reviews/RNBWJTW1SCICE?ASIN=B01HQCKG4O','Reviewed in India on 11 July 2024','Product is durable and good for use','True','B01HQCKG4O','POSITIVE'),(3394,4,'Nice product','https://www.amazon.in/gp/customer-reviews/R3ONHDJRB29Q4Z?ASIN=B01HQCKG4O','Reviewed in India on 25 July 2024','Tight the cap well then use it work properly','True','B01HQCKG4O','POSITIVE'),(3395,4,'Good product','https://www.amazon.in/gp/customer-reviews/R2YB0VV8QWTMQG?ASIN=B01HQCKG4O','Reviewed in India on 20 July 2024','good product a value for money product..','True','B01HQCKG4O','POSITIVE'),(3396,5,'Great product','https://www.amazon.in/gp/customer-reviews/R30K4FN4Q9VFKW?ASIN=B0BDVN579S','Reviewed in India on 12 June 2024','It\'s good and , good for plants I seen changes after using it regular intervals I saw growth , flowering and good potential to plants , ..no smell