ne  without an O ring .This product deserves nothing less than 5 stars and those who gave less than 5 stars for reasons other than leakage have overlooked the product.Since it is a pressure sprayer designed for  watering and spraying pesticides to plants and not  to replace any pressure wash for cleaning cars or algae. Every product is expected to perform some function and never discontent with that only because it is not performing some other function.This is purely a manual pressure sprayer designed to sprinkle pesticide or water at a nominal pressure and for the same purpose 120 or 140 bar is not at all required.It cannot be used to clean vehicle as the pressure is not at all sufficient for self cleaning without wiping.','True','B01AUPGA9Y','POSITIVE'),(3690,4,'Intended for Rooftop gardeners','https://www.amazon.in/gp/customer-reviews/R2VT3423H73H3D/ref=cm_cr_arp_d_rvw_ttl?ie=UTF8&ASIN=B01AUPGA9Y','Reviewed in India on 28 August 2022','If you have 150-200 pots to feed liquid nutrients, this is the best option for you. But for 600 pot owners, I would suggest a full 16 litre sprayer. I have to feed at least 9-10 litres of liquid to my plants time to time, so I preferred this 8 litre sprayer, which is light weight and easy to carry. Kissankraft sprayer comes with two types of carrying system. One can hang it from soldier by strap or can carry by handle. I prefer the second one. The pumper has a locking system and locked pumper becomes carrying handle. The sprayer nozzle and pipe can cover 5 feet radius, so positioning it nearby a set of pots, drenching them and carrying it in another spot is less tiresome than all time carrying it by strap.Pumper is very easy going. At least 30-32 push is necessary in a set and you have to repeat it a few times to spray full 8 litre. Nozzle rod is made of plastic, light weight and sturdy. Same is true for the body parts.There is a convenient pressure release valve and a sprayer push lock to continue spraying without a fatigued finge