C6LB8PJ/ref=cm_cr_arp_d_rvw_ttl?ie=UTF8&ASIN=B08D8CHZ9C','Reviewed in India on 3 February 2024','Organic fertilizers are derived from natural sources and provide nutrients to plants in a slow and sustainable manner. They are an excellent choice for environmentally conscious gardeners and farmers. Here are some common types of organic fertilizers and their benefits:Compost:Source: Decomposed organic matter, such as kitchen scraps, yard waste, and manure.Benefits: Rich in organic matter, compost improves soil structure, water retention, and provides a balanced range of nutrients. It enhances microbial activity in the soil.Manure:Source: Animal waste, such as cow, chicken, or horse manure.Benefits: A good source of nitrogen, phosphorus, and potassium. Manure also adds organic matter to the soil and helps improve soil fertility.Bone Meal:Source: Ground bones, usually from cattle.Benefits: High in phosphorus, bone meal is beneficial for flowering and fruiting plants. It contributes to root development and overall plant strength.Fish Emulsion:Source: Fish waste and remains.Benefits: Provides a quick source of nitrogen, as well as phosphorus and potassium. It is often used as a liquid fertilizer and promotes vigorous plant growth.Blood Meal:Source: Dried and powdered animal blood, usually from cattle.Benefits: High in nitrogen, blood meal is excellent for promoting leafy green growth in plants. It\'s a fast-acting organic fertilizer.Seaweed/Kelp Fertilizer:Source: Extracts from seaweed or kelp.Benefits: Rich in trace minerals, seaweed fertilizer enhances plant growth, improves stress resistance, and promotes overall plant health.Cover Crops:Source: Various plants grown to cover and protect the soil.Benefits: Leguminous cover crops, like clover, add nitrogen to the soil through a process called nitrogen fixation. Cover crops also prevent erosion and improve soil fertility.Green Manure:Source: Plants, such as legumes, that are grown and then plowed back into the soil.Benefits: Adds organic matter, improves soil structure, and releases nutrients as it decomposes.When using organic fertilizers, it\'s important to note that they release nutrients more slowly compared to synthetic fertilizers. Patience is key, as organic fertilizers contribute to long-term soil health and sustainability. Additionally, the choice of organic fertilizer may depend on the specific nutrient needs of the plants and the soil conditions. Always follow recommended application rates to avoid over-fertilizing.','True','B08D8CHZ9C','POSITIVE'),(4097,3,'Fertiliser is not good for plants','https://www.amazon.in/gp/customer-reviews/R1MIVWVPW0BG2Y/ref=cm_cr_arp_d_rvw_ttl?ie=UTF8&ASIN=B08D8CHZ9C','Reviewed in India on 8 July 2024','Waste of money.','True','B08D8CHZ9C','NEGATIVE'),(4098,5,'It\'s good for growth of my plant','https://www.amazon.in/gp/customer-reviews/ROSHU7S2AKR1Z/ref=cm_cr_arp_d_rvw_ttl?ie=UTF8&ASIN=B08D8CHZ9C','Reviewed in India on 7 May 2024','I brought this format plants good growth','True','B08D8CHZ9C','POSITIVE'),(4099,4,'Best for plant','https://www.amazon.in/gp/customer-reviews/R239B4YSKHVCOK/ref=cm_cr_arp_d_rvw_ttl?ie=UTF8&ASIN=B08D8CHZ9C','Reviewed in India on 10 March 2024','It\'s really good','True','B08D8CHZ9C','POSITIVE'),(4100,1,'Appears to city waste compost Not vermi compost','https://www.amazon.in/gp/customer-reviews/R2MBM6RVGB21B5/ref=cm_cr_arp_d_rvw_ttl?ie=UTF8&ASIN=B08D8CHZ9C','Reviewed in India on 21 June 2024','Please do not from this supplier, It do not appear to be vermi compost at all. It appears he has dampen the city waste compost. City waste compost is harmful to plants. It is too much acidic. Ones I lost about 50 plants due to application of city waste compost.','True','B08D8CHZ9C','NEGATIVE'),(4101,5,'looks legit','https://www.amazon.in/gp/customer-reviews/R3DSRSA0WN86EH/ref=cm_cr_arp_d_rvw_ttl?ie=UTF8&ASIN=B08D8CHZ9C','Reviewed in India on 31 August 2023','its not very dry so I was able to see some live baby worms on it and I 