7Z55JV6','Reviewed in India on 6 May 2018','My second similar purchase from Field agro. This product is very good, a few things to share:1 – The pump would auto-off when the output water flow is stopped, and would auto-on when you let the water flow again; this is a pressure pump.1 – You would get good pressure ONLY if you use a watergun that has the little hole at front, and not a \"circle\" type, from where water is ejected, see picture. The pump works similar to an RO pump, but differently than a jet/monobloc pump.2 – If you face problem with the threaded design at pump output, simply pass a usual garden pipe (½\") over it, and tighten it with the metal-ring with the bolt (available commonly at any hardware store, see picture - I\'ve loosened the ring to get a good view). This gives better result than using the small plastic pieces given along with the unit. The water inlet uses a ¼\" pipe, see picture.3 – I used 12 V Battery of a UPS (you can solder two wires from the battery terminals). But the unit consumes good amount of current, so be sure that the copper wires from battery to unit are thick enough, else it would heat up, and the unit would not get proper current.','True','B077Z55JV6','POSITIVE'),(5762,2,'The Pump is good; seller sucks.','https://www.amazon.in/gp/customer-reviews/R23NOYHUOJOW4O/ref=cm_cr_arp_d_rvw_ttl?ie=UTF8&ASIN=B077Z55JV6','Reviewed in India on 13 June 2018','The overall pump is good. But I did receive a faulty product, where one of the motors were not working. Didn\'t return but repaired it myself. The seller should have checked before sending or might be they have checked and sent the faulty one.Also, the seller sends the pump without any heat shrink wrap or any waterproofing on the motor terminals. They should have done that.And an adapter jack with all the connections done would be appreciated.The force of water coming out of the pump is very good. I used it to wash my car and bike, and it does the job brilliantly. 4.5 stars on that.'